Season 11

The tenth season of Dancing with the Stars premiered 22 March 2010.

There was no elimination the first week of competition. The first elimination took place 30 March.

Tom Bergeron returned as host. Season 7 champion Brooke Burke replaced Samantha Harris as host. Len Goodman, Bruno Tonioli, and Carrie Ann Inaba all returned as judges.

On 25 May 2010, singer Nicole Scherzinger and Derek Hough were announced as the winners; figure skater Evan Lysacek and Anna Trebunskaya placed second and ESPN host Erin Andrews and Maksim Chmerkovskiy placed third.

Pamela Anderson returned to compete in the all-stars season and was the first celebrity to be eliminated.

Development[]

College Dance Championship[]

Four colleges were featured in a tournament-style competition. Three individual episodes featured two colleges competing against each other in a one-dance showdown. The judges provided individual scores following each performance.

On 11 May 2010, UC San Diego (dancing the Samba) competed against Purdue (dancing the Mambo). Purdue advanced to the finals, with viewer votes offsetting their 24 to 22 deficit in judges' scores. The 18 May episode featured Rutgers and Utah Valley. Both teams danced the Cha-Cha-Cha, and Utah Valley won the dance-off with their score of 29 over Rutgers' 21. In the finals (25 May), Utah Valley (dancing the Samba) topped Purdue (who danced the Cha-Cha-Cha) for the championship.
